      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the base",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Line a 20 cm springform tin with baking paper. Process the stoned {{medjool-dates}}, {{desiccated-coconut}}, {{walnuts}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}} in a food processor until the mixture comes together as a sticky mass. Press firmly and evenly into the base of the tin. Freeze for 30 minutes while you make the filling.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Blend the filling and set, 8 hours",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Drain the soaked {{cashews}} and rinse well. Blend with the {{coconut-oil}}, {{maple-syrup}}, {{lemon-juice}}, and {{vanilla-extract}} until completely smooth, at least 3 minutes. Pour over the frozen base and smooth the top. Freeze for at least 8 hours or overnight.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Top and serve",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Remove from the freezer 5 minutes before serving. Release the springform and arrange the {{blueberries}} and sliced {{strawberries}} over the top. Slice with a sharp knife dipped in hot water and dried between cuts. Return any leftover cheesecake to the freezer.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
